Now to demonstrate the issue:
The filter is initialized on component load with the default "TestText"
![demo1](https://github.com/dotnet/aspnetcore/assets/3234246/9e4f00a1-56cb-491f-9bf6-727bd29a7edc)

Modifying this text and applying the filter passes the correct changes to the parent component
